# Normalize all text files to LF in the repository on every platform,
# regardless of `core.autocrlf`. Keeps line endings consistent and stops
# editors/formatters on Windows from silently committing CRLF — which otherwise
# flips a touched file's whole content in the diff (`\r\n` vs `\n` on every
# line). `text=auto` lets git auto-detect binary vs text; `eol=lf` forces LF for
# anything detected as text.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets — never normalize (git usually auto-detects these, but be
# explicit so a stray heuristic never rewrites them).
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.webp  binary
*.ico   binary
*.ttf   binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.pdf   binary

# Grammar test fixtures (`.sd`) are read byte-for-byte by the snapshot tests,
# and the `.snap` / `.vsc.snap` baselines are generated on LF checkouts. Force
# LF for both on every platform so the snapshot suites are byte-stable
# regardless of `core.autocrlf` — without this, a Windows checkout rewrites the
# fixtures to CRLF and every newline-bearing snapshot diffs (`"\r\n"` vs
# `"\n"`, span lengths off by one per line). See GRAMMAR.md §17.
*.sd    text eol=lf
*.snap  text eol=lf
